
<h1 class="text-center text-primary py-2">Welcome to Recipe App</h1>

<div class="container text-center">
  <h2>
    <i>Recipe app keeps track of all your recipes, ingredients, and inventory. 
    It will allow you to save ingredients, keep track of what you have, create recipes, 
    and generate a shopping list based on what you have and what you are missing from a 
    recipe. Also, since sharing recipes is an important part of cooking the app should 
    allow you to make them public so anyone can access them.</i>
  </h2>
  <h3 class="text-info py-2">To use the app you need to create an account and log in.</h3>

 
</div>
<div class='px-5'>
  <h2 class="text-center pt-5 text-primary">Public Recipes for some users</h2>
  <div class='container'>
  <% if @recipes.length > 0 %>
    <% @recipes.each do |recipe| %>
        <div class='row my-3 border card border-4 p-3'>
          <%= link_to recipe_path(recipe ) do %>
            <div class='col'>
              <h2><%= recipe.name %></h2>
              <h4>By: <%= recipe.user.name %></h4>
            </div>

            <div class='col-8 fs-5'>
              <p>Total food items: <%= recipe.count_total_food_items %></p>
              <p>Total price: $<%= recipe.count_total_price %></p>
            </div>
          <% end %>
        </div>
    <% end %>
  <% else %>
  <h2 class="text-center card py-2 text-info">No public recipes yet</h2>
<% end %>
  </div>
</div>
